{"product_id": "12100", "page": 15, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-28", "text": "\"Grand Theft Auto III\" is a classic that created a whole new genre of video game that dominates the industry today. I first played this game on the PS2 when it was still fairly new and spent dozens and dozens of hours playing it to full completion. While it looks and plays fairly crudely in 2017, I believe it is still a worthwhile use of your game-play time. It remains a fun experience once you get back into the 2001 mindset. The atmosphere and world building is still impressive today as well as the amount of missions and side-quests to accomplish.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "JonathanDP81", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 15, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-28", "text": "Grand Theft Auto III is the perfect example of a groundbreaking title that still is just as enjoyable today. Arguably the most controversial game of 2001 and the first massive success in the video game industry of a post 9/11 world, GTA III is a game about revenge, murder and chaos. Set in the fictional New York-inspired Liberty City, you take control of a mute named Claude. He and his girlfriend Catalina are escaping from a bank heist when she turns on Claude, shooting him and leaving him on the ground for the police to find minutes later. A few days later while on a transfer to the city's detention centre a car intervenes with the convoy and frees the prisoners while also managing to destroy the bridge the event took place on.\nThe game contains a great open world that was extremely impressive back in the year of release. It has a good story but admittedly it's not very in-depth. The soundtrack is full of fantastic songs from the main theme's relaxing piano to the various radio stations filled with a selection of liscensed and original tracks. The graphics are still pretty decent by today's standards but the character models have not aged that well. There is oodles of activities and situations to get yourself into in Liberty City.\nOveral this game is a masterpiece that will keep you playing for a long time and it's something I can reccomend even to detractors of the sandbox genre.", "hours": 54.4, "username": "Super Cosmo Pines! [SGB]", "products": 175, "early_access": false}
