{"product_id": "12100", "page": 33, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "PROS\n+ Set a solid foundation for 3D GTA and sandbox games as a whole\n+ Soundtrack is catchy once it grows on you\n+ As always with GTA games, it's fun to go on rampages\nCONS\n- Limited guns\n- Nothing to do with money besides spend it on guns. armor and ammo\n- Super small soundtrack\n- Game gets tedious towards the last third of the game\nIt might seem like I hate GTA3, but I don't. It's a fun game, especially to go back and see what they did here that they did in future games. From the perspective of someone who played it in 2001 I get why people called it one of the best games ever. From the perspective of someone playing it in 2017, Vice City and San Andreas blow this game out of the water.\nSCORE: 7/10", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Squash Thompson", "products": 201, "early_access": false}
