{"product_id": "12100", "page": 47, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-04-12", "text": "It kills me having to downvote this game. GTA 3 was my second ever GTA game back in the day on the PS2 (I started with Vice City). GTA 3 is such a nastalgic game for me and that's why I decided to purchase it for PC. Unfortunatley this is one of the worst PC ports I have ever played. I would actually deem the game UNPLAYABLE. First, the menu is invisible. If you want to change graphics settings or play a differnt save from the main menu, too bad. Second, there's a glitch where every car in the game has a weird black shadow on them, you can't even see the cars. It's a sad and truly pathetic effort by Rockstar and it's\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665poor of Steam to allow this game to be up for sale. Rockstar please fix. Until then DO NOT make a purchase with this game.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Saucy Dangles", "products": 93, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
