{"product_id": "12100", "page": 53, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-08", "text": "In 2001 Rockstar Games released one of the most ambitious games they had ever released to the public. Grand Theft Auto III was the first game ever to start what has culminated today in one of the greatest games known in videogaming. Being the first open world game to feature polygonal tridimensional models, it started a trend that would continue to evolve until this very day. Rockstar Games is known to many as a Publisher that invests everything in their games because they want to excel in what they do and they want to deliver to the public. With GTA III it is shown how that set of mind started and how each Publisher and/or Developer should treat their IPs.\nGTA III has a fun story plagued with satiric comments to Pop Stars and the way of life of the era it is situated in, in this case the 2000's. If you've not played this game at all, I won't spoil the story, but damn it's 2017! You better start playing it!\nWhile right now GTA V surpasses in every way the now outdated GTA III, it still is a fun game to play to reminisce about how it all started, and let's be honest, doesn't matter how polygonal the city or characters are, it's always fun to smash your car against other cars and shoot everything that moves, because GTA is mayhem and that's why you are going to buy this game!\nSo, ready to go back to Liberty City my friend?\n8/10\nBuy it, play it and don't regret it.", "hours": 1.6, "username": "jesusrey91", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 53, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-07", "text": "I will always love gta 3 due to it being one of the first games I ever loved on the ps2", "hours": 49.4, "username": "Likely Hates You \u265b", "products": 32, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 53, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-05", "text": "GTA III for me is a classic. Takes me back to my PS2 days of looking up cheat codes, and turning all of Liberty City into a battle ground. Cars instantly explode when they hit the tank, and the OP assault rifle can destroy the entire motor pool of police cars in a single magazine. It's good to be back!", "hours": 5.1, "user_id": "76561198006440452", "username": "101st Steel Legion", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 53, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-03", "text": "I can't review this game, my nostalgia is thicker than PEASOUP (cheat code to make stage 3 foggy weather)\nthe nostalgia is so thick that I just can't review this honestly without feeling overwhelmed by how much fun this game brought me when I was a kid (even though I played vice city for nearly 14 hours each day, this game was played significantly less but for some reason I like it MORE!)\nTHIS GAME and Vice City were basically my childhood and I loved EVERY police chase, shootout, mission (even though I never finished the games) and I still can't get enough of these games\nmain reason why I like them: small map with memorable landmarks so you are NEVER lost (unlike GTA 4 and GTA 5)", "hours": 0.7, "username": "Ramona Andersen", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
