{"product_id": "12100", "page": 55, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-24", "text": "Anyone wanting to know how to make a open world shooter, GTA3 should be lesson #1.\nLiberty City is split into 3 islands. Each with their own neighbourhoods. Each neighbourhood has its own look and gang.\nThe side missions, alone, make for great fun: drive a taxi, be a vigilante (hunting bad guys in car chases), drive an ambulance or fire engine.\nThe story missions take you on an interesting journey, working your way up the mafia ladder (for starters).\nThe downsides are the lighting seems way too dark on most models. Also, lighting normals seem to be non-existant. This seems to be a thing for this era of game. I don't know whether it is that normals are broken, or they just are not there.\nDefinitely recommended, if on sale.", "hours": 36.2, "username": "-|WaD|- BigMike\u2122", "products": 141, "early_access": false}
