{"product_id": "12100", "page": 57, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-21", "text": "Quite glitchy as is (On Windows 10 at least, MacOS version is alright). I installed SilentPatch with DDraw (should fix the invisible menu glitch), GInput (for xbox controller  support), a widescreen fix patch, and reduced mouse sensitivity to the minimum. Now the game is playable. I hope that helps any Windows 10 users out there.\nRockstars should consider uploading a remastered steam version for GTA classics that support Windows 10, widescreen monitors, and xbox controllers.\nNot worth the full price. Stick to the mobile version for now. Wait for Steam / Humble bundle sales and only buy as part of a discounted GTA collection.", "hours": 14.4, "username": "Moe", "products": 172, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 57, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-21", "text": "Still worth playing for the main missions; like I said top-notch voice acting and cut -scenes. A bit plain, but it was the first full 3d GTA; no more bird's eye view.", "hours": 14.2, "user_id": "76561197987175590", "username": "BlastFromTheJollyPast", "products": 161, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 57, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-19", "text": "What a truley Atmospheric Gem this game is. Modern games have definetly uped the anty, but there's just something about this game and the world that it creates, everything just comes together, and creates a gritty but loveable playground to be explored. If you can ignore graphic limitations and rubish controls, but enjoy an rich atmosphere presented to you, It's a must play.", "hours": 52.2, "user_id": "76561198337329741", "username": "lockete11899", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 57, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-17", "text": "Despite my low play time reported on steam for this game, I have played this game for many hours on both the PlayStation 2 and the PC as well.\nDon't Bother with this one. Beyond it being the first fully 3D Grand Theft Auto game, and one of the first games to do 3D open worlds well (being a massive improvement over Driver and Driver 2 before it), there's very little here that was not either also done or done better in GTA Vice City and/or San Andreas. Beyond the main story (and the payphone side missions), the only things left to do is collect hidden packages, cause general mayhem and do the police, firefighter, and taxi side missions.\nContrast this with GTA Vice city where you have all of that with better and more weapons, better and more cars, better gang distribution (seriously, after a certain point in GTA 3\u2019s story, one area of the map becomes impossible to drive through without a tank, as gang members who wield shotguns in that area will shoot at you and will blow up your car immediately upon entering their territory), better and less linear\nstory line missions, MUCH better music (Beyond the station with the Scarface OST and the Rap Station I distinctly remember the music in GTA 3 being pretty awful) and a more interesting city with better aesthetics. All of this remains true for San Andreas, which managed to improve it beyond what even Vice City improved upon, making it that much more significantly better than GTA 3. For the most part, the liberty city of GTA 3 was depressing to look at, with a lot of grey in the colour palette, whereas for both of its successors, this was significantly improved. What I will say in GTA 3's favour is that its simplicity makes it good for a mobile game, compared with the more complex controls of Vice City and (especially) San Andreas.\nOverall, don't buy this, at least not on PC, and instead buy GTA San Andreas or Vice City. Unless you're replaying it for nostalgia purposes or on your phone/tablet, there's nothing here that hasn't been done better in other 3D open world games since. If you REALLY want to play in the Liberty City of GTA 3 on PC, search for mods to add Liberty City into either GTA San Andreas or Vice City, you will get the city of GTA 3 with the improvements of VC or SA.", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561198055312449", "username": "random_person21", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 57, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-17", "text": "GTA 3 is simply the best because well... IDK.\nI had a slight issue when launching on Win 8.1, it wouldn't launch without DirectPlay. It'll happen on Windows Vista and over (7, 8, 8.1, 10, 10AU) but it happens on VC and SA as well. AT LEAST there is no GFWL requirement, as 7 and under have that, 8+ crash.\nOverall, my rating is 8.5/10.", "hours": 18.2, "username": "Tide Pod", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
