{"product_id": "12100", "page": 72, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-16", "text": "It certainly hasn't aged all that gracefully, but damn if it hasn't left a still noticable impact on the gaming landscape as we know it. There's a lot that can be said about Grand Theft Auto III, from the initial media perception to how it shaped free roam and open world. But at this point why bother when I can ask the simple question; Is it a good game?\nWell sort of, as mentioned prior GTA III hasn't aged that well, although still tolerable it lacks many refinements brought by later franchise entries and you'd likely not play it as much as you would years ago upon release as more enjoyable games exist. However this is not to say the campaign itself isn't worth playing, it may not be as well written as the likes of IV or even VC but it has it's own charm ignoring obvious clich\u00e9s and maybe you'll get something out of seeing how far GTA has come.", "hours": 20.9, "username": "iN008", "early_access": false}
