{"product_id": "12100", "page": 92, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-20", "text": "A long time ago, it may have been a playable product, but age looks down upon games with a mighty fist, and Grand Theft Auto 3 is no exception. Featuring incredibly poor camera controls for both vehicles and on foot, terrible shooting controls, wonky combat, lack of checkpoints or even a basic mission restart, GTA 3 should serve only as a reminder of GTA's roots or a reminder that we've come a long way since then.", "hours": 2.9, "username": "Gondile", "products": 680, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
