{"product_id": "12100", "page": 106, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-28", "text": "A great open world game, inspired by the likes of the Godfather trilogy and Scarface. With the authentically recreated city of New York (Liberty City) to explore, a great soundtrack, fun gameplay and a dramatic plot, this game is a real classic.", "hours": 101.6, "username": "Aymin", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 106, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-28", "text": "The first game in the series - a classic!\nDid not age well. I hate the timed missions. No character stats (as in GTA:SA).\nThe plot is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.\nAnyway, buy this game on sale for the collection.\nGTA:SA is better in all regards. If you are new to the series start with San Andreas. You will not be disappointed.", "hours": 14.8, "username": "Zinda", "products": 261, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 106, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-23", "text": "After playing all the other GTA games in the series, I never really got too far into the game back on the PS2, so I recently bought it again on here to complete it.\nThe game's performance is perfect and the visuals despite being dated are still very nice to look at, especially when you download the Widescreen Mod, so I have been playing this in 1080p like a remaster.\nI also would reccomend the GInput mod, as it gives you 100% Xbox 360 controller functionality, and has made the game just as playable as the later games in the series.\nI would like to point out I am playing on Windows 10, without a hitch.\nOverall I recommend this game as the story is great and it is definitely worth another play just for it.", "hours": 11.6, "username": "Josh", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
