{"product_id": "12100", "page": 124, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-22", "text": "Created well before Rockstar's rush towards modernization in the series, GTA III plays in an arcade-y style in almost every way, from combat, to aesthetic, to vehicle handling. The more barebones plot may put off those coming straight in from narrative-heavy titles, but the plot's never in your face or repetitive. You'll encounter ton of hilarious banter/dialogue as you build influence and respect in Liberty City. This game ranks a little higher in difficulty than some others in the series at times, and features a nice variety of missions. Rockstar's first GTA entrant into 3D is a winner.", "hours": 15.1, "username": "I Gotcha Back", "products": 339, "early_access": false}
