{"product_id": "12100", "page": 129, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-26", "text": "The game that put the Grand Theft Auto series on the map if you were like me and played the old school gta's which had bad graphics and a ugly top down camera. This thing blew your mind. I spent hours on this game as a kid and it still has it's replay value to this day.\nYes it misses features from later games such as buying property and motor bikes amongst other things but this game is still top notch.\nThe story of gta 3 and aswell as the variety of missions are superb.\nGameplay is simple (You can get patches for xbox 360/ps3 controllers from the gta garage community site that work like a charm)\nLots of ways to customise the game such clothing, altering the maps VIA GAME FILES.\n10/10", "hours": 20.2, "username": "Mithras O_+", "products": 933, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 129, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-23", "text": "The game that single-handedly reinvented the open-world sandbox genre is just as much fun today as it was way back in 2001. The dark and grimy streets of Liberty City provide endless opportunities for exploration, experimentation and unabashed carnage. Guns, explosions and car chases, the holy trinity that has more or less become the bread and butter of the GTA series, were first brought to the forefront with this game. If you can look past the old-gen graphics and sometimes blocky textures, what you'll find is one of the most iconic games of all time, as well as one of the most infinitely replayable.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "Tominator", "products": 69, "early_access": false}
