{"product_id": "12100", "page": 135, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-11", "text": "This was the first open-world video game that I played back when I was 7 years old. Trust me, I didn't even know what I was doing because I had just arrived in America at that time and my computer seemed to have a problem with allowing me to play it normally cause the screen would go black every 5 minutes and I'd have to change the camera view to get it back to normal. Suffice to say, I've managed to reconcile the problem since then (15 years ago) and it works beautifully. I suggest modding it a bit to make it look and play like a more modern GTA of today. (OnePiece's HD Cars and Tri-Pack plus some much needed improved HD city textures will allow it to look a bit more fresh) It's a classic and one of the best GTAs to try and get 100% in since it's one of the easiest to do so in. Also, I recommend switching out Steam's EXE with a regular 1.1 version if you want to avoid the dark colored cars problem. Editing the TXD file works too but changing the EXE won't break the game. If anything, it'll allow more mods to work since some don't work with Steam's version. Overall, it's still a good game even in today's modern period and holds up well even without mods.", "hours": 253.7, "username": "Iggy Wolf", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 135, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-10", "text": "It may be old, but it's a GTA, and in fact it's THE Grand Theft Auto that marked a milestone in the gaming industry and the very first title in the franchise to be in 3D. It's simply one of those classics you should play at least once.\nMaybe it's just nostalgia talking, but the game is still enjoyable after all its years. I recommend installing the Xbox graphics mod though, so it all looks a little nicer. Amazing soundtrack as always, not very complicated missions (yet fun to play through), great humour (the radios get me everytime) and the very first appearance of Catalina! Loved it!\nDefinitely get it and play this piece of gaming history. Oh, and just try to keep it brief when talking to Claude, unless you w...*bang*", "hours": 11.1, "username": "JJ", "products": 618, "early_access": false}
