{"product_id": "12100", "page": 143, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-31", "text": "This game opened so many doors, so many eyes.  I think players new to the GTA franchise would probably be better served with one of the newer titles, but for someone like me who played this game when it first came out, and plenty more after that, this game is a well-remembered old friend.  I have been known to sit in an idle vehicle in some quiet corner of the city, just listening to the talk radio station in the rain.  Memorable characters and challenging quests with dated graphics, but still enjoyable and most certainly recommended.", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561197993368900", "username": "RustyBaker", "products": 155, "found_funny": 16, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 143, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-31", "text": "Grand Theft Auto 3 is the landmark game that made the jump shift to 3D back in 2001. Before that, previous GTA games where in 2D top down perspective.\nAs the series progressed, none could have achieved without the stepping stone of this game. Even thou the controls are very clunky, story is very plain, and outdated gameplay compared to the recent entries.\nStill a very great game to this day!\n7/10.", "hours": 5.6, "username": "GrimVenomReaver", "products": 396, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
