{"product_id": "12100", "page": 154, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-27", "text": "GTA III is back when Grand Theft Auto was still kind of brutal.  The dark atmosphere and the fact that the game is always during the nighttime is really unhelpful and just doesn't feel like it fits the ridiculous pretentions the GTA games in the past and in the future embodied.  GTA IV is certainly an improvement on the idea, but GTA III has enough good ideas that I can let it get away with it.  Everything is really dynamic, cars don't spin out like there's grease on the wheels, although there is a blighting lack of bikes, the narrative is solid and even though the BJ Blascowitz lookalike doesn't talk and therefore has no personality, there's nothing objectivly bad with it.  It's a fine and fair reminder of where all this began.", "hours": 1.5, "user_id": "76561198055465598", "username": "Kid Cuisine", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
