{"product_id": "12100", "page": 157, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-06", "text": "Grand Theft Auto III is literally a landmark and pinnacle achievement in game development.\nHaving only briefly played the first GTA back in the late 90's on a friend's Playstation (I had,well, still have, an N64. Works fine too.) I didn't know what the craze was all about when this masterpiece was originally released in 2001. I watched another friend play it for days on his PS2 while his great dane stared at me. The only thing I gathered was the silent protagonist could go on shooting sprees and kill \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s. I hadn't paid much attention to the story. But having finally laid my hands on the PC copy (on Steam of course, only thing I laid my hands on were a 360 controller) I grasped the unique and ubiquitious narrative with excitement.\nOf course I knew the sandbox formula in the GTA universe. I'd played through GTA IV several times in 2008 and even beat Liberty City Stories on the PSP! (I'd also played GTA: San Andreas prior to this, just a few months ago). So I knew what to expect. I knew the characters, I knew the story, mostly, and knew the gameplay.\nIt might be 2014, but the 3D graphics are still interesting, the camera work that was chosen; cinematic and professional, the dialogue; true to the gangs' styles. What really makes the game is the satirical take on violent societies as well as the strangeness authenticity to cities such as NY or LA.\nNot the greatest game storywise, but still enjoyable when you consider that Claude, although emotionless and silent, is the most badass protagonist.\n9.5/10", "hours": 19.3, "user_id": "76561198009430218", "username": "JacoRay", "products": 774, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 157, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-05", "text": "Okay gameplay (something between VC and SA), pretty nice graphics, but thats all. Story line for this game is -1/10, literally there is no story line. Random and nonsense movies before missions, main character who dont say a word in whole game and context... Yes, context is missing here totally. Just awfull comparing to San Andreas or Vice City. And music in all radio stations just wasnt for me, used my own playlist from PC what isnt good thing for game IMO. And yes, I know, this game is more like old GTA's - just for missions, but still I cant handle missing story line here. Just for missions and default GTA stuff this game will be ok i guess.", "hours": 12.4, "username": "shevijs <3 S1mbaa", "products": 579, "early_access": false}
