{"product_id": "12100", "page": 157, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-03", "text": "Okay, here's what I'm going to say right now.\nThis game is great and all, but I'm going to have to say that San Andreas was probably much better than this. The confusion begins when the first mob hates you and then, literally, every mob hates you. You can't complete the game or leave your PC without getting shot. You can't drive more than five minutes without getting shot. You can't even get on or off the subway without getting headshot oh so suddenly.\nI understand\u2026 you make everyone hate you, but if it means it breaks the enjoyment of the game, then I guess I'm sticking to GTA:SA, GTAIV, or even GTAV.", "hours": 5.8, "username": "\u5f90 \u00a6 \u30a2\u30ec\u30c3\u30af\u30b9", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
