{"product_id": "12100", "page": 157, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-02", "text": "GTA3, the game that brought open-world gameplay to the mainstream.\n5/5 Stars.\nNote: My review is based on the original CD-ROM release for PC and the PS2 version, so my Steam stats don't reflect my actual play time with GTA3.\nPros:\nHUGE open-world, which seems to live on its own.\nPopouri of various game types: shooting, driving, racing, melee.\nExcellent sense of humor with Pop culture references.\nLOW hardware requirements; a netbook could run GTA3.\nGamepad support, both Direct Input (Logitech) and Xinput (360 controller).*\nCons:\nOld, 6th gen (PS2/Xbox/Gamecube/Dreamcast era) graphics.\n*Direct Input controllers automap exactly like the PS2 version.", "hours": 2.2, "username": "hare1222", "products": 610, "early_access": false}
