{"product_id": "12100", "page": 170, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "A great game that I had much fun with going back a few years on PS2. The controls are easy to get a grips with and for a price of \u00a32.99 you can't go wrong. This game is all about the nostalgia of being back in Liberty City with 2002 graphics. But to be honest, graphics on these old GTA's never matter if you are a true GTA fan. The story line is as gripping as ever, also I reccommend once completed that you try out different cheat codes and mods to give a little more fun because once this game is completed it can be a little tedious to play. However, the game is an absoloute classic and goes down in my books as one of the best in it's era. :)", "hours": 1.5, "username": "Sket", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 170, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "Pros: Holds up really well. The city feels real, alive, with different sections inhabited by different groups/gangs(Chinatown, the Mafia's turf, etc.). All of the radio channels are worth listening through. Sharp satire, much of which remains applicable. Cars, boats and a plane to use. A ton of stuff to do, keeping you playing long after you've completed the storyline. Cool story, with twists and backstabbings - a proper big city crime story. Great mission design.\nCons: Shooting is pretty bad(they did realize, and put more emphasis on car-missions, thankfully). The early-ish 3D graphics have really aged. Barely a personality to the protagonist.\nMy recommendation: a must for any fan of open-world gaming.", "hours": 36.7, "user_id": "76561198019557045", "username": "A.G.B.", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 170, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "Grand Theft Auto III is the game that led the \"open world adventure\" video game era. Grand Theft Auto is personally my favorite video game series, and Rockstar hasn't given me a reason for it not to be. The game is usually $5 on big sales, and I picked it up during the Winter 2013 Sale. The missions are challenging, and there are tons of them. Side quests, main missions, sensitive controls and physics. Try ramming a car into a streetlight, or a try pushing a car with a fire truck for a while. This game promises hours of fun and goofiness, while at the same time coming off as serious and meaningful. Enjoy the game, 10/10.", "hours": 14.5, "username": "ploq tacku", "products": 269, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 170, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-26", "text": "Good game, a bit outdated by today's standards, but still fun and hard as balls (Oh yes, these aren't your everyday balls, these are THE balls).", "hours": 25.3, "username": "Flying Hippo", "products": 197, "early_access": false}
