{"product_id": "12100", "page": 172, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-07", "text": "While it does have its moments, overall it's fairly uninteresing. The different factions shooting and sometimes insta-killing you makes the exploration of the city more frustrating than fun. Plus it's not like there's much to explore in this somewhat empty city. Aside from the generally mediocre story missions there's just not a lot to do in this game.\n5/10", "hours": 13.1, "username": "Dr. Monolight", "products": 918, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 172, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-06", "text": "The first notable Grand Theft Auto game exploded on to the scene, effectively birthing the Action-Sandbox game genre. The plot is massive, and the random AI makes for interesting encounters, as well as side quests that ensure that no playthrough will be the exact same. Even straying from the main story line for the entirety of your playthrough will not leave you disappointed.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "Sinew2", "products": 337, "early_access": false}
