{"product_id": "12100", "page": 173, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "I was a big fan of the original top-down Grand Theft Auto games.  I was totally psyched when GTA III came out.  A 3-d Grand Theft Auto game?  This is going to be great!\nThen I got it.  What a laggy, poorly-coded pile of excrement.  This thing allegedly had Playstation code in it.  I'm talking about the PC version.  Absolutely unplayable on computers of the day.  I was a huge Grand Theft Auto fan but after this debacle, I completely got off the series.\nOver ten years later, on a modern computer, the game doesn't lag.  Much.  Maybe in another decade computers will be developed that will be able to run this poorly-coded garbage.  It's otherwise a fun game at times.\nPwninator score: 3/10", "hours": 1.6, "username": "Pwny McPwnPwn", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
