{"product_id": "12100", "page": 177, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-28", "text": "Grand Theft Auto III, What a classic in my eyes. The story in this game is really good and enjoyable, but it is really short. The game has aged quite a bit in the graphics department , but it's still fun. If you plan on using a controller with this game, get ready to fight with the camera. The Music in this game is excellent, I find myself listening to these songs even after so many years. When installing the Steam port, I had a lot of problem with textures, but a simple patch fixed all that. I can't say Grand Theft Auto III is the best choice for someone looking for a first time GTA game. It's aged and story is really short. I would say pick up Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas, Grand Theft Auto: Vice City, or Grand Theft Auto IV for a first time GTA player. It's still a good game even so.\n4/5 - Wonderful", "hours": 32.1, "username": "Rinoa Poison", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
