{"product_id": "12100", "page": 181, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-21", "text": "The best in the GTA games, city to remember great characters this was Liberty City at its best...GTA has not been same since. I first played this on the Playstation 2 big change into the new 3D engine at the time. For the playstation 2 this was a big leap forward with plenty to explore, rich characters, fun weapons & making the star signs go up being in a mad city police chase. Other GTA titles have done well but never matched this titles story & urban city feel, Certainly one of the greatest games in history.", "username": "BoXMaN-RipPeR", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 181, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-02-18", "text": "Grand Theft Auto III is the most infuriating sequel since Half-Life 2 - for all of us lore junkies, it's just a real trying time. Where has Claude gone after the end of GTA2? Why have we gone back in time twelve years? Why are the graphics so bad now compared to the stylised magic of the previous instalment?\nRockstar should have just given up while they were ahead. And don't get me started on the numbering system from this one onwards, none of it makes any sense! Actually, what's the deal with this one - isn't this actually Grand Theft Auto IV?! How dare Rockstar ignore London 1969?!", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Solid G", "products": 336, "early_access": false}
