{"product_id": "12100", "page": 182, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-03", "text": "GTA II was already fun, but GTA III took the franchise to a whole new dimension (literally). At its time it was ground breaking: an open realistic world, fantastic sound track and voice acting,  cool characters and endless possibilites.\nYou could just drive through the city listening to music, do crazy stunts, kill cops or play as a cop/ taxi driver etc. The only bad points are some clipping errors and the mediocre shooting system.\nEven to this day the game is very enjoyable if you don't mind dated graphics.", "hours": 44.9, "username": "core", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
