{"product_id": "12100", "page": 185, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-25", "text": "This revolutionary game (which I played mostly on PS2) changed how big and open games could be and how much you could interact with them. Rockstar made a game that players could, for the first time, roam around a 3D 'open world' all the while stealing cars, driving like a mad man and shooting or driving over anything that moves.\nThe atmosphere and social commentary of (fictitious)1990's U.S. culture and media, delivered through the dialog, car radios and advertisements, is both accurate and controversial. The radio advertisements in particular are so over the top and funny but also disgustingly realistic. I loved the classical radio station in GTA III and wish that one will be in GTA IV.\nFor me, the unique thing that set GTA III apart from the GTA games that followed are the quirky and stylized look and physics. Some of the most fun I've had with GTA III was driving how you should never drive a car in real life.\nIn my top five games of all time list.", "hours": 24.2, "username": "Bungles Bob", "products": 627, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 185, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-14", "text": "It's a great and original concept, even though it has some downsides such as crashing opening video screens, terrible menu glitches in which it's invisible, poor FPS settings.\nFor the actual game I think it's very repetitive, but what most people like about it is that it's an open world. Gameplay, graphics and the characters are neat and I love how the protagonist is silent.\nJoystick support is terrible, it does not feature auto aim nor does the joysticks work properly.\nOrginality and an open world environment is what makes this boat sail. I thought the story was fairly alright.\nimdbScore: 7.5/10", "hours": 15.9, "username": "\u00b0treetoon", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 185, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-01", "text": "Word of warning: The mac version in steamplay is just WINE. So it runs like butt. It'd probably run better in a VM.", "username": "The Day It Snowed In Dixie", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 186, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-03-31", "text": "While I never got around to totally playing this one entirely... I did watch my brother play it everyday and played it a few times. My main beef with it was the square controls and strange driving mechanics.\nIt was the first 3D GTA so it gets props, but I wouldn't say that I would recommend it now because its really dated.", "username": "McMillanFixXxeR", "products": 414, "early_access": false}
