{"product_id": "12100", "page": 188, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-24", "text": "Grand Theft Auto is the definitive answer to all the critics of violence in video games. It simply smashes all those statements allowing you to kill anyone you see, destroy everything and have a good time too. It raised a lot of controversy that did nothing but help the sales, my guess is that it's the best card Rockstar has under their sleeve (and don't forget Jack Thompson). The series have seen a new life within 3D graphics, making Rockstar Games, become superstars. These days it's easy to see the faults of the game, but it's a very nice nostalgic feeling of returning to this world of crime and violence... Ah good days.", "hours": 34.5, "user_id": "76561198030305825", "username": "Anderson", "products": 284, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12100", "page": 188, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-23", "text": "A classic like no other. The story is silly - why they decided for a silent protagonist is beyond me, but the missions past the initial tutorials are generally good and fun (and lucky don't bring \"morality\" or \"film-like plots\" into it much). Very tough end game and not a great deal to do outside of missions but there is a lot of gameplay, and in spite of dated graphics it holds up remarkably well, with just about every modern GTA's gameplay mechanics in plain sight - something to mull over when contemplating any future ones since most of it has been done before.", "username": "Finaldeath", "products": 623, "early_access": false}
